ActorTalk: This is a vulnerable species from the Golden Age—Stellar Asparagus, family Asparagaceae, genus Asparagus.
It has relatively short flower stalks, but its leaf-like branches are longer and straighter than those of the Fern Asparagus. It's very unique! Everyone, please take a look—
Where's my asparagus? Who stole my Stellar Asparagus!
It doesn't look like... an asparagus at all.
Seems like it's not growing according to your description.
